# üêû bug report

### Description

When I use ContentChildren with RouterLink or RouterLinkWithHref and then try to update the container with ViewContainerRef.createEmbeddedView, then ContentChildren stops returning results.

```typescript
// TODO(issue/24571): remove '!'.
@ContentChildren(RouterLink, { descendants: true })
links !: QueryList<RouterLink>;

// TODO(issue/24571): remove '!'.
@ContentChildren(RouterLinkWithHref, { descendants: true })
linksWithHrefs !: QueryList<RouterLinkWithHref>;
```

Template:

```html
<p *appUnless="false">
    This paragraph is displayed because the condition is false.
    <a routerLink="/another-page">my link</a>
</p>
```

Code:

```typescript
ngAfterContentInit(): void {
    console.log("links length", this.links.length);
    console.log("linksWithHrefs length", this.linksWithHrefs.length);
}
```

I tried [asking on stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54139543/contentchildren-wont-load-any-data-when-querying-routerlink-and-routerlinkwithh), but didn't find a solution.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
You can see this behavior in [this stackblitz](https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-rkkp6z). This [other one](https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-segeto) shows that it works without the call to ViewContainerRef.createEmbeddedView.

